    9. Myocardial enzyme spectrum is within the normal range (for example, simple laboratory abnormalities that are judged by the investigator to be of no clinical significance are also allowed to be included in the group);
14. For female participants of childbearing age, a urine or serum pregnancy test should be performed within 3 days before receiving the first study drug administration (day 1 of cycle 1)and the result should be negative . If the urine pregnancy test result cannot be confirmed as negative, a blood pregnancy test is required. Women of non-bearing age are defined as at least 1 year after menopause, or have undergone surgical sterilization or hysterectomy;
15. If there is a risk of conception, all participants (whether male or female) need to use contraceptive measures with an annual failure rate of less than 1% during the entire treatment period until 120 days after the last study drug administration.

